data.title: Yusuf Dikec’s new swag: Pistol turns to beer can. Elon Musk joins the meme celebration
data.meta_description: Turkish shooter Yusuf Dikec became an internet sensation following his silver medal win in the mixed 10m Air Pistol event at the Paris 2024 Olympics. Noted for his relaxed style and casual attire, Dikec's fame was further boosted by social media interactions, including a meme shared by Elon Musk.
data.text:
Synopsis

Turkish shooter Yusuf Dikec became an internet sensation following his silver medal win in the mixed 10m Air Pistol event at the Paris 2024 Olympics. Noted for his relaxed style and casual attire, Dikec's fame was further boosted by social media interactions, including a meme shared by Elon Musk.

Turkish 'hitman' Yusuf Dikec continues to be in news. World richest man continues to like and shares posts about the new internet sensation. Tesla founder shared a meme featuring Dikec, 51, who secured a silver medal in the mixed 10m Air Pistol event at the Paris Olympics 2024 and went viral for his shooting style.

In his post on X, Musk shared a popular Dikec meme, a modified video by social media users, possibly with the help of Artificial Intelligence (AI). After Dikec fires his pistol, the pistol transitions into a can of beer and he is seen . He gulping it down that redefines his epic swag.

Earlier, the Turkish shooter asked Musk if the billionaire industrialist foresees robots, with "hands in their pockets", in shooting events at the Olympics in the future.

"Hi Elon, do you think future robots can win medals at the Olympics with their hands in their pockets? How about discussing this in Istanbul, the cultural capital that unites continents?" Yusuf Dikec had asked.

Soon after Yusuf Dikec won the medal, social media users couldn’t help but obsess over his unique and casual approach to competitive shooting. His unorthodox style, which included wearing standard glasses and yellow earplugs instead of elaborate protective gear, has made him an internet sensation.

You Might Also Like:

Did Olympic fame Yusuf Dikec pick up shooting as revenge after divorce? Here is the real story

The Turkish Olympic shooting silver medallist had earlier said he was surprised by his new-found fame, after his casual style with no headwear and a hand in his pocket made him an overnight Internet sensation.

Yusuf Dikec and partner Sevval Ilayda Tarhan won silver on for Turkey in the mixed team 10m air pistol, losing to Serbia in the gold medal match.

But it was Dikec's posture that caught attention as much as the result, with the marksman wearing standard glasses, a team T-shirt and with his left hand casually slung in his pocket.

You Might Also Like:

Is Olympic fame Yusuf Dikec really that cool in real life? His colleague shares the truth

Other than his pistol, he notably had none of the specialised equipment used by athletes in the hyper-precise event, like headphones, special lenses or a hat.

"Be cool like Yusuf Dikec. Congratulations on winning the silver medal in such a cool way," France's embassy to Turkey wrote in a post on X in Turkish.

"The name's Dikec. Yusuf Dikec," said posts by other users in reference to cinema icon James Bond. Some memes added a cigarette to his mouth to emphasise the relaxed posture.

You Might Also Like:

Yusuf Dikec has more style: His 'both eyes open' shooting technique even stuns Olympics referees

Speaking to Turkish channel TGRT Haber, Dikec acknowledged that he had adopted the rare technique of shooting with both eyes open whereas most athletes keep one closed or obscured.

"My shooting technique is one of the rare shooting techniques in the world. I shoot with both eyes open. Even the referees are surprised by this," he said.

He said winning a medal was no surprise as "this year we prepared a lot and worked a lot... this success belongs to all of Turkey."

"Success doesn't come with your hands in your pockets."
